-- Four U.K. Companies Ending Water Use Restrictions After Rains
-- B y   W h i t n e y   M c F e r r o n
-- 2012-07-09T10:16:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-09/four-u-k-companies-ending-water-use-restrictions-after-rains.html
Four U.K. water companies are ending
restrictions on the resource use after recent heavy rains, the
National Farmers Union said.  South East Water ,  Sutton and East Surrey Water ,  Veolia
Water Central  and  Veolia Water Southeast  have lifted bans on
outdoor watering, the NFU said today on its  website . All four
companies confirmed ending the hosepipe bans on their websites.
Three other companies, Thames Water, Anglian Water and Southern
Water, lifted similar  restrictions  in June, according to the
U.K. Environment Agency.  To contact the reporter on this story:
